\par Abstract: This paper presents a new framework for coping with problems often encountered
\par when modeling seasonal high frequency data containing both flow and stock variables.
\par The idea is to apply a multivariate weekly representation of a daily periodic model and
\par to exploit the possible cointegration and common feature properties of the variables
\par in order to obtain a more parsimonious model representation. We introduce the
\par notion of common periodic correlations, which are common features that co-vary -
\par possibly with a phase shift - across the di?erent days of the week and possibly also
\par across weeks. The paper also suggests a way of modelling the dynamic interaction
\par of stock and flow variables within a periodic setting that is similar to the concept of
\par multicointegration among integrated variables. The proposed modelling framework
\par is applied to a data set of daily arrivals and departures in the airport of Mallorca.
