\par Abstract: The AEL consists of empirical macro studies of the effects of development aid. At the end of 
\par 2004 it had reached 97 studies of three families, which we have summarized in one study each 
\par using meta-analysis. Studies of the effect on investments show that they rise by 1/3 of the aid \endash  
\par the rest is crowded out by a fall in savings. Studies of the effect on growth show an 
\par insignificant positive effect. Studies of the effect on growth, conditional on something else, 
\par have till now shown weak results. The Dutch Disease effect of aid has been ignored. The best 
\par aggregate estimate is that since its start in the early 1960s aid has increased the standard of 
\par living in the poor countries by 20%.
